Food was sooooooo goood
Good food a bit pricey small dark setting

I went here on a double date and I enjoyed everything. My boyfriend recommended I try the rum punch so we all had that and it was tasty. He also told me about the sesame salmon so I decided to get that which came with sautéed veggies and I chose Mac & cheese as a side. Delicious!! The salmon was so flavorful, the veggies were mixed in with a nice sauce and the Mac was really cheesy with a slight crisp on top just how I like it. The other couple with us really enjoyed their food as well. Food came in a decent amount of time, very hot and fresh. There was no complaints! I recommend coming here during the week if you want a quiet night or during the weekend if you want a party/club scene. They also offer brunch which I am going to try out soon.
The music was more like for a club versus for a dining  atmosphere. The food was just ok and drinks was over powered by the rum

I went to Hush Restaurant on Sunday December 13th for brunch for my birthday. The atmosphere was beautiful with nice music. My girlfriends and I ordered some tasty appetizers and delicious drinks. I ordered the steak omelet and my friends had the steak and eggs, and the lobster and grits plate. The food was seasoned well, cooked just right, and left us feeling full and satisfied. We were very pleased with our selections. We will return again for more delicious food. Chef Roe really did his thing.
i had the salmon and it was so good. taste and presentation was everything. thanks chef roe! I will be back.
Ayo this is the best darn brunch at a black owned restaurant where you can dine in and enjoy the game! Anywhere Chef Roe is, the food is always bomb. Once again....KABOOOM! You did it again!

Visiting from DC and my friend took me to Hush.  I must say That Brunch, My Gawd!! It didn’t disappoint!! Lobster and grits and a red velvet waffle on the side lol Fn scrumptious!! Not to mention the bottomless mimosas 😜 The service was great too!! Chef Roe And Kash were awesome!!

HUSH RESTURANT AND LOUNGE PHENOMENAL, We went there for Sunday brunch. The atmosphere is cozy, and clean. I had the Red velvet waffles and spicy chicken, my significant other had grits with oxtails. Omg I thought he was going to lick the plate, he barely came up for air. The staff are very accommodating, professional. This is a resturant and lounge that you need to put on you bucket list.

Arrived early group of 4 meet & greet @ the door seated promptly. Reviewed the menu saw they had special for the brunch. Ordered bammy sliders w/ackee @salt fish great The wife had the crab cake/island salad which was very good. My guest ordered bbq wings,chicken & waffles Skirt steak home fries & eggs shrimp & Cajun grits Oxtails & grits 😎 All items well seasoned & cooked perfectly 😎 Thx HUSH 🦾❤️ Well be back😎

I went for the brunch with my son and we ordered oxtail n grits n fry shrimp and fries we enjoyed the music and the food was amazing I follow chef roe on ig and seen some of his pictures of the food so I said let me try it I will be back foe this week brunch

I had Sunday Brunch with my cousins this past weekend.  The food tasted so good. It was cooked very well and the presentation of the food made it even better.  The service was professional and the waitress was kind and very patient. Hostess greeted us with a very welcoming smile!!!!
I went this past Sunday for Brunch and the food is Absolutely delicious. Chef Roe is amazing from presentation to flavor. Fancy food for your Soul. Definitely returning for Brunch!!

The food was absolutely delicious 😋 the amiunce of the restaurant was impeccable. My hostess was very kind and sweet. I will definitely visit HUSH again. Thank you HUSH for such an wonderful experience
Small intimate lounge. Food was amazing. Drinks were on point. Staff was super nice and customer service was exceptional!
Food is good and cozy
We went for our monthly girls night out. The food was delicious and prepared fresh. Drinks were great. We had outdoor seating. The ambiance was reminiscent of a NYC rooftop with awesome music.

Tonight marks my 3rd time at this restaurant, and I must say I was disappointed 😞 - I made a 9pm reservation for 3 people & we arrived around 7:45pm & sat at the bar. We ordered appetizers & drinks a talked until our reservation was up. By 9pm, I asked the hostess 3x when we would be seated. She kept saying soon, but it wasn't until I asked the owner that we finally were given a table.  Once seated, we waited for what seemed like forever for service. It was our friend's birthday so we really wanted tonight to be nice for her, but the service just got worse as the night wore on. Our waitress took forever to address us, she never checked on us throughout the night & a lot of service went to the outdoor area. Perhaps this is why we were made to wait so long for service inside! My first 2 times here were phenomenal! I had a blast! The food was really good, the dj & whole vibe was on point! I don't know what happened tonight. Not only was the service NOT good, but there were TOO MANY people there! To boot, our waitress took so long to bring our check, that we had to go to the bar on our way out to close our bill. Hush better get it together or they may be hushed!

i don't understand how this place still stay in business. they refuse to give you food for your money. i order a sesame fish take home to my wife , i wish i had opened the bag before took it home, i was like no food in the plate literally 4 small piece of so call fish like piece of potatoes  $24. i have never seen anything like this. an addition to long wait. it best to sea your money
Very nice outdoor dining area.  Food delicious and drinks not watered down.  Fish sticks made from actual fish fillet.

The staff are HORRIBLE. They are more concerned with having interpersonal relationships amongst themselves than actually providing great customer service. Waitress and hostess were extremely unprofessional. Would never want to be served by them again.The 1 star is for the Chef and his delicious, fresh, well cooked and seasoned food.

I visited this establishment over the weekend for the second time .The hostess asked if we had reservations. We didn't ,while she was trying to explain that they were at full capacity inside and outside.A tall gentlemen with glasses rudely approached the hostess stand  yelling" We are at full capacity " multiple times to me and other guest waiting in the crowded walkway.He then began speaking yelling at the  hostess .His behavior was unprofessional and unessessary . He needs to be trained on customer service skills.Also teens came into the business and were not asked for Id's .After 10 pm  unbelievable ! An establishment that serves alcohol didn't  ask for Id's from kids who appeared to be under eighteen . This is one of the reasons so many venues of color don't succeed! I will support where I'm provided with great customer service .Even if I can't be accomodated at that time.
Always a great time when I visit this restaurant, it is NEVER a disappointment. Keep up the great work guys.

This restaurant has an outside ambience that is very up beat! The food is great the drinks are great as well. What needs help is the waiters and hospitality! We were seated very fast on a Saturday night surprisingly the inside of the restaurant was full (im sure way over covic restrictions.) We were seated outside, we seen three different waiters no one came to our table to ask if we needed water for over 45min now I know u would wonder why would we stay there? The answer is I wanted to know exactly how long was a waiter going to come! Not soon after wqiters did show just NOT FOR HOUR TABLE! THE FIRST PICTURE U SEE WERE DRUNKS THAT WERE BOUGHT AT THE BAR ! AT THAT POINT I WAS JUST COMPLETELY DISAPPOINTED! All the beautiful reviews and we had to walk to the bar to order food to go and our own drinks ! For ur high prices u need to upgrade ur customer service!

This used to be a lounge called “‘magnet” and now it’s hush . It’s new and the place looks clean and nice . My only complaint would be the customer service don’t get me wrong the waitress is attentive but the wait for the food was way too long . My dad had to wait 35 mins for a salad otherwise though the food was worth the wait because it was good and even the Mac and cheese was good and if you know even though Caribbean’s can cook Mac and cheese isn’t their speciality but this restaurant did a good job with the Mac . It’s a nice lowkey Jamaican restaurant I hope they grow more over time . They play music but it’s not too much where you can’t hear the person you’re with talking . Definitely come here as a calm date night spot

Great Ambiance and good food. Wait a bit longer than expected but if prepared, the occasion can be a fantastic experience. Manager Ron has done a great job. My family and I can't wait for a revisit.

Food was great!  Good vibes!  Great place to hang with friends and family!

This is my new go to restaurant. The atmosphere is wonderful. Great DJ. He was doing his thang! The live band was an awesome surprise. The food was sooo fresh and tasty. Yum! The staff was also very friendly and personable. It's not too big or small, just the right size. This place gets 2 thumbs up for me. Can't wait to go back.

This place was ridiculously over priced. Music extremely loud for no apparent reason. The food nasty, rice and peas tough and dry. Took almost an hour for the food to arrive at the table.  Would never in life return to this place. They call it Hush  for a reason.  And the service is no good.  Just all around  terrible place .

The food was amazing!  The waiter "Chris" (same name as one of the owners) was very good.  The place was very clean and the music very subtle  - makes you want to linger and enjoy your food and conversation.  Definitely going back again and again.  Telling my friends and colleagues about it.

Absolutely love this place . From the moment you walk in the ambiance is mind blowing . The food was fresh, properly prepared and a great value for the price. The menu is perfect, something for everyone. My favorite is the lobster and shrimp fried rice and the seafood special on Wednesday’s is to die for !!! I’m not much of a drinker, however I tried the hush cocktail and it was very refreshing. For a Caribbean restaurant, I absolutely love the diversity of the workers and the professionalism they displayed. The service was superb!!!! I highly recommend this restaurant.

Everything from the atmosphere to the ambiance, food, service & drinks was amazing! Perfect for a datenight, very low key ...music is at a level fit for uninterrupted conversations. Definitely going back!!!
Such a dope ambiance! The interior is very nicely designed and the staff is very attentive from the minute you walk through the door. The Hush cocktail was wonderful and so was the music.
